work.agda (1316 lines) - Added helper functions, classification theorem, and DNF/CNF bridges.

New imports:
- Cubical.Data.Sum (⊎, inl, inr) for classification disjunction

New components in OrthogonalGens:
1. evalConj-negLits: evalConjClause (negativeLiterals ns) = finMeetNeg ns (inductive bridge)
2. evalDisj-posLits: evalDisjClause (positiveLiterals ns) = finJoin ns (inductive bridge)
3. classifyElement: every element is ∥ (joinForm ns) ⊎ (meetNegForm ns) ∥₁
4. getIndices: extract index list from OrthoNF
5. isJoinForm: Bool check for which form
6. orthoNF-to-DNF/CNF: convert OrthoNF to general DNF/CNF data types
7. orthoNF-to-DNF-correct / orthoNF-to-CNF-correct: evaluation correctness
8. simplifiedDNFExists: every element has a simplified DNF
9. simplifiedCNFExists: every element has a simplified CNF

The classifyElement theorem is the key result from CLAUDE.md:
"argue that there is either only conjunctions of negations of generators,
or disjunctions of non-negated generators"

Status: All compiling, no postulates, no holes.
